this file is created on github for leaning about pull command
commands include to learn through this file:
1.git fetch - fetch the logs about what changes made on the online repository on github what you lag behind and have to pull those changes locally (only logs not even visible yet)
2.git checkout origin/main - this temporarily changes the whole local repo to the repo present online on github , and used to view what changed that you don't implemented on local level means(not pulled)
3.git switch main - this bring you back to your local repo mode on vscode which is actual working directory you were working on and not have new changes locally yet,its just a undo of git chechout command
4.git pull - this finally update your local working directory with all the changes form the online repo on github (logs + actual files)
